m_series)"}
{"title_page": "Sarah Mezzanotte", "text_new": "'''Sarah Mezzanotte''' is an American actress.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gerard|first=Jeremy|title=Sarah Mezzanotte Cast As Jessica Par\u00e9\u2019s Younger Self In Amazon\u2019s \u2018The Interestings\u2019|date=25 February 2016|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|url=https://deadline.com/2016/02/sarah-mezzanotte-the-interestiongs-amazon-jessica-pare-1201709157/|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>  She is known for playing Marnie in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Chambers (TV series)|Chambers]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Thompson|first=Avery|title=Sarah Mezzanotte Breaks Down Marnie\u2019s\u2018Complicated\u2019 Relationship With Sasha In\u2018Chambers\u2019 & More|date=26 April 2019|publisher=[[Hollywood Life]]|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2019/04/26/chambers-sarah-mezzanotte-interview-netflix-show/|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>  She is a co-recipient of the 2017 [[Obie Award]] for Best Ensemble for her work in Sarah DeLappe's ''[[The Wolves (play)|The Wolves]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cox|first=Gordon|title=\u2018Oslo,\u2019 \u2018The Band\u2019s Visit\u2019 Score 2017 Obie Awards (Full List)|date=22 May 2017|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)]]|url=https://variety.com/2017/legit/news/obie-awards-2017-full-list-oslo-1202440209/|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>  She also received a special [[Drama Desk Award]] for Outstanding Ensemble for her work in ''The Wolves''.<ref>{{cite web|last=McPhee|first=Ryan|title=2017 Drama Desk Awards Presented June 4|date=4 June 2017|publisher=[[Playbill]]|url=https://www.playbill.com/article/2017-drama-desk-awards-presented-june-4|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Select filmography==\n*''[[Blame (2017 film)|Blame]]'' (2017)\n*''[[Central Park (2017 film)|Central Park]]'' (2017)\n*''[[Drunk Bus]]'' (2020)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|6310745}}\n* {{IBDB name|513808}}\n* {{iobdb name|47938}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Obie Award recipients]]\n[[Category:Drama Desk Award winners]]\n", "text_old": "'''Sarah Mezzanotte''' is an American actress.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gerard|first=Jeremy|title=Sarah Mezzanotte Cast As Jessica Par\u00e9\u2019s Younger Self In Amazon\u2019s \u2018The Interestings\u2019|date=25 February 2016|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|url=https://deadline.com/2016/02/sarah-mezzanotte-the-interestiongs-amazon-jessica-pare-1201709157/|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>  She is known for playing Marnie in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Chambers (TV series)|Chambers]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Thompson|first=Avery|title=Sarah Mezzanotte Breaks Down Marnie\u2019s\u2018Complicated\u2019 Relationship With Sasha In\u2018Chambers\u2019 & More|date=26 April 2019|publisher=[[Hollywood Life]]|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2019/04/26/chambers-sarah-mezzanotte-interview-netflix-show/|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>  She is a co-recipient of the 2017 [[Obie Award]] for Best Ensemble for her work in Sarah DeLappe's ''[[The Wolves (play)|The Wolves]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cox|first=Gordon|title=\u2018Oslo,\u2019 \u2018The Band\u2019s Visit\u2019 Score 2017 Obie Awards (Full List)|date=22 May 2017|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)]]|url=https://variety.com/2017/legit/news/obie-awards-2017-full-list-oslo-1202440209/|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>  She also received a special [[Drama Desk Award]] for Outstanding Ensemble for her work in ''The Wolves''.<ref>{{cite web|last=McPhee|first=Ryan|title=2017 Drama Desk Awards Presented June 4|date=4 June 2017|publisher=[[Playbill]]|url=https://www.playbill.com/article/2017-drama-desk-awards-presented-june-4|accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Select filmography==\n*''[[Blame (2017 film)|Blame]]'' (2017)\n*''[[Central Park (2017 film)|Central Park]]'' (2017)\n*''[[Drunk Bus]]'' (2020)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|6310745}}\n* {{IBDB name|513808}}\n* {{iobdb name|47938}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Obie Award recipients]]\n[[Category:Drama Desk Award winners]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarah_Mezzanotte"}
{"title_page": "Jensen (surname)", "text_new": "{{Infobox surname\n| name = Jensen\n|image= \n|imagesize= \n|caption= \n| pronunciation =\n| meaning = \"Son of Jens\"\n| region = Scandinavia\n| origin = \n| variant = Johnson \n}}\n\n'''Jensen''' is a surname of [[Scandinavian languages|Scandinavian]] origin.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.houseofnames.com/Jensen-family-crest/German|title=Jensen Name Meaning, Family History, Family Crest & Coats of Arms, German|website=HouseOfNames}}</ref> Jensen literally means ''son of Jens''. In the 2001 it was the most common surname in Denmark,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.surnamemap.eu/denmark/surnames_ranking.php|title=Denmark surname ranking|last=Ravara|first=Stefano|date=|website=Surname Map|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> but nowadays it is the second most common surname in [[Denmark]], where it is shared by about 5% of the population.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dst.dk/Statistik/Navne/pop/2007.aspx |title=Archived copy |access-date=2007-11-10 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012023436/http://www.dst.dk/Statistik/Navne/pop/2007.aspx |archive-date=2007-10-12 |df= }} Statistics Denmark</ref> It is also very common in other Scandinavian countries such as [[Norway]], where it is the ninth most common [[surname]], but nevertheless shared by about 5% of the population. The name is also in use in the [[Faroe Islands]].\n\nThere was no \"Jensen family,\" merely a system of patronymics that was finally fixed in the 19th century at an arbitrary time, when the state bureaucracy required family names; before that people took their name from their father's first name.<ref>Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges, ''A Dictionary of Surnames'' (Oxford: Oxford University Press, 1988), pp. xxxv & 282-83.</ref>\n\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==List of persons with the surname==\n\n{{compact ToC|side=yes|top=yes|num=yes}}\n\n===A===\n*[[Adolf Jensen]] (1837 \u2013 1879), Composer\n*[[Al Jensen]] (born 1958)\n* [[Alex Brian Jensen]], Danish darts player\n* [[Anabel Jensen]], American educator and author\n* [[Anders Thomas Jensen]] (born 1972)\n* [[Anne Elisabet Jensen]] (born 1951)\n* [[Arthur Jensen (actor)]] (1897\u20131981)\n* [[Arthur Jensen]] (1923\u20132012)\n* [[Ashley Jensen]] (born 1969), British actress\n* [[Axel Jensen]] (1932\u20132003)\n\n===B===\n* [[Betty Lou Jensen]]\n* [[Bhumi Jensen]] (1983\u20132004)\n* [[Bjarne Jensen (umpire)]] (born 1958), Danish cricket umpire\n* [[Bj\u00f8rg Eva Jensen]] (born 1960)\n* [[Brian Jensen (footballer born 1968)]], Danish football defender, played six games for the Danish national team\n* [[Brian Jensen (footballer born 1975)]], Danish football goalkeeper, played more than 200 games for English club Burnley\n* [[Benjamin Jensen]] (born 1975)\n* [[Barry Jensen]] (Professional Rugby League Footballer) born 1954\n\n===C===\n* [[Captain C. W. Jensen]], American policeman in Oregon\n* [[Carsten Jensen]] (born 1952)\n* [[Christian Jensen (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Christoffer Jensen]]\n* [[Claus Jensen]] (born 1977)\n* [[Cornelius Jensen]] (1814\u20131886), Danish sea captain and Californian politician\n\n===D===\n* [[Daniel Jensen]] (born 1979), Danish footballer\n* [[Darren Jensen]] (born 1960)\n* [[David Jensen]] (born 1950)\n* [[David A. Jensen]] (born 1965)\n* [[Debra Jensen]] (born 1958)\n* [[Dennis Jensen]] (born 1962)\n* [[Derrick Jensen]] (born 1960)\n* [[Dick Jensen]] (born 1942, died 2006) Hawaiian entertainer \"The Giant of Hawaii\" \n* [[Ditte Jensen]] (born 1980)\n* [[Doron Jensen]] (born 1958), American restaurateur \n* [[Dorte Juul Jensen]]\n* [[Dwight Jensen]]\n* [[David Jensen]] (born 1982), American investment advisor\n\n===E===\n* {{ill|Egon Jensen|sv|Egon Jensen}}  (1928-1985), Danish politician. \n* [[Eirik Jensen]] (born 1957), Norwegian drug trafficker and former policeman \n* [[Elaine Jensen]] (born 1955)\n* [[El\u00edn Metta Jensen]] (born 1995) Icelandic footballer\n* [[Elwood V. Jensen]] (1920\u20132012), American biologist\n* [[Eric Jensen (racing driver)|Eric Jensen]] (born 1970)\n* [[Eric A Jensen]], American and British professor\n* [[Erik Flensted-Jensen]] (1908\u20131993)\n<!--* [[Eugene \"Gene\" Jensen]]-->\n* [[Eugen Jensen]] (1871-1957)\n* [[Eulalie Jensen]] (1884\u20131952)\n\n===F===\n* [[Frank Jensen]] (born 1961)\n\n===G===\n* [[Georg Jensen]] (1866\u20131935)\n\n===H===\n* [[J. Hans D. Jensen]] (1907\u20131973)\n* [[Hayley Jensen]] (born 1983)\n* [[Helene Jensen]], Danish female curler, European champion\n* [[Henning Munk Jensen]] (born 1947)\n* [[Henrik Wann Jensen]] (born 1970)\n\n===I===\n* [[Ingrid Jensen]] (born 1966)\n\n===J===\n\n* [[Jackie Jensen]] (1927\u20131982)\n* [[Jacob Jensen]]\n* [[James A. Jensen]] (1918\u20131998)\n* [[Jane Jensen]] (born 1963)\n* [[Jane Jensen (musician)]] (born 1968)\n* [[Jelena Jensen]] (born 1981)\n* [[Jens Jensen (politician)]] (1865\u20131936)\n* [[Jens Jensen (landscape architect)]] (1860\u20131951)\n* [[Jens Fink-Jensen]] (born 1956)\n* [[Jesper B. Monberg|Jesper B. Jensen]] (born 1977), speedway rider\n* [[Jim Jensen (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Joakim Jensen]], Norwegian professional ice hockey player\n* [[Johan Jensen (boxer)|Johan Jensen]] (1898\u20131983), Danish boxer\n* [[Johan Jensen (mathematician)|Johan Jensen]] (1859\u20131925), Danish mathematician\n* [[Johannes Vilhelm Jensen]] (1873\u20131950)\n* [[John Jensen (disambiguation)]]-for John Jensen, Jon Jensen, Jonathan Jensen or Johnny Jensen\n* [[Jorgen Arendt Jensen]], Danish engineer\n* [[J\u00f8rgen Jensen (athlete)|J\u00f8rgen Jensen]] (1944\u20132009)\n* [[J\u00f8rgen Christian Jensen]]\n* [[Judy Jensen]] (born 1953)\n\n===K===\n* [[Karen Jensen]] (born 1944), American actress\n* [[Karolina Jensen]] (born 2003), Danish curler\n* [[Kirsa Jensen]], 14-year old New Zealand girl who disappeared in 1983\n* [[Klavs F. Jensen]] (born 1952), chemical engineer\n* [[Kris Jensen]] (musician, born 1942)\n\n===L===\n* [[Larsen Jensen]] (born 198